## Africana Studies Relation

The Pittsburgh Crawfords represent the intersection of sports, business, and African-American resilience during segregation. Their success highlights Black excellence and community unity in the face of systemic racism. The Crawfords' legacy serves as an important study in Africana Studies, showcasing how Black entrepreneurship and athleticism thrived despite racial barriers.

